### <a id="2-10-33"></a> v2.10.33

**Release Date:** March 07, 2022

<div class="note warning"><strong>Warning:</strong>
  This release includes a new version of BOSH DNS that requires Ops Manager to redeploy all VMs.
  <br />
  <br />
  This version of BOSH DNS requires every BOSH DNS certificate to have a Subject Alternative Name (SAN). A migration was introduced in <%= vars.ops_manager %> v2.10.9 to add SANs to these certificates. Upgrade to v2.10.9 or later and do an **Apply Changes** on all VMs before you upgrade to this patch. If you do not complete this migration first, you might experience BOSH DNS resolution issues until the change is rolled out to all VMs.
  <br />
  <br />
  To check whether the migration has been succesfully run on all VMs, see <a href="https://community.pivotal.io/s/article/How-to-Verify-Bosh-DNS-Certificates-Have-Correct-SAN-Fields?language=en_US">How to Verify Bosh DNS Certificates Have Correct SAN Fields</a>.
